WEBVTT

00:04.471 --> 00:05.405 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Good evening. I'm
Gwen Ifill.

00:05.439 --> 00:07.207 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And I'm Judy
Woodruff.

00:07.241 --> 00:11.178 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: On the "NewsHour"
tonight: As
the Justice Department releases
a transcript

00:11.211 --> 00:17.284 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of the Orlando shooter's 911
call, the Senate
takes up gun control, and the
Supreme Court

00:17.317 --> 00:20.520 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
upholds assault weapons bans in
two states.

00:20.554 --> 00:25.859 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Also ahead, a
report on the
ground in Fallujah, where Iraqi
government

00:25.893 --> 00:30.797 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
forces are closing in on ISIS
militants holed
up in the key city.

00:30.831 --> 00:36.470 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Plus, a big Trump
campaign staff
shakeup, as Democrats take a
summer lead in

00:36.503 --> 00:39.439 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
polling and fund-raising. It's
Politics Monday.

00:39.473 --> 00:45.746 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And the world's
most popular
modern art museum, London's Tate
Modern, builds

00:45.779 --> 00:49.016 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
upon its pioneering history with
a new 10-story
wing.

00:49.049 --> 00:52.886 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NICHOLAS SEROTA, Director, Tate
Modern: I
think that maybe we helped to
open up the

00:52.920 --> 00:59.092 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
idea of what a museum could be,
that the experience
of visiting a museum should be a
learning

00:59.126 --> 01:01.662 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
experience, but it should also
be a social
experience.

01:01.695 --> 01:05.365 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

01:05.399 --> 01:09.636 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:09.670 --> 01:24.084 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The FBI today
released transcripts
of the 911 calls made by the
gunman in Orlando.

01:24.117 --> 01:29.356 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In them, Omar Mateen pledges
allegiance to
the leader of the Islamic State
group, and

01:29.389 --> 01:32.960 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
says the U.S. should stop
bombing Iraq and
Syria.

01:32.993 --> 01:37.497 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Initially, this morning,
officials released
partial transcripts, without the
references

01:37.531 --> 01:39.199 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
to ISIS.

01:39.232 --> 01:41.368 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RONALD HOPPER, FBI Assistant
Special Agent
in Charge: Part of the redacting
is meant

01:41.401 --> 01:45.439 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
to not give credence to
individuals who have
done terrorist acts in the past.

01:45.472 --> 01:50.277 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We're not going to propagate
their rhetoric,
their violent rhetoric. And we
see no value

01:50.310 --> 01:53.914 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in putting those individuals'
names back out
there. We're trying to prevent
future acts

01:53.947 --> 01:58.618 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
from happening again. And for
cowards like
this one, people like that
influence them,

01:58.652 --> 02:01.088 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
so we're not going to continue
to put their
names out front.

02:01.121 --> 02:05.792 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Republicans
criticized the
decision, and, hours later, the
Justice Department

02:05.826 --> 02:07.661 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
put out more complete
transcripts.

02:07.694 --> 02:13.333 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: In the presidential
campaign,
Vice President Joe Biden went
after Donald

02:13.367 --> 02:16.903 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Trump today over his calls for
action against
Muslims.

02:16.937 --> 02:22.576 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In a Washington speech, the vice
president
didn't directly name the
Republican nominee-to-be,

02:22.609 --> 02:24.244 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
but his target was clear.

02:24.277 --> 02:26.947 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOSEPH BIDEN, Vice President of
the United
States: Wielding the politics of
fear and

02:26.980 --> 02:32.919 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
intolerance, like the proposal
to ban Muslims
from entering the United States,
profiling

02:32.953 --> 02:40.861 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Muslim Americans, slandering
entire religious
communities as complicit in
terrorism, calls

02:40.894 --> 02:44.798 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
into question America's status
as the greatest
democracy in the history of the
world.

02:44.831 --> 02:51.104 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Also today, Trump
fired his longtime
campaign manager, Corey
Lewandowski. The campaign

02:51.138 --> 02:57.277 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
gave no reason, and Lewandowski
did not report
that he'd alienated members of
Trump's family.

02:57.310 --> 03:02.015 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Asked on CNN why he was let go,
he said, "I
don't know the answer to that."
We will dig

03:02.049 --> 03:03.917 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
deeper on Politics Monday.

03:03.950 --> 03:08.755 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: A searing heat
wave peaked
today in the Southwestern U.S.,
with temperatures

03:08.789 --> 03:15.562 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
expected to hit 120 degrees in
some places.
The triple digits are breaking
50-year-old

03:15.595 --> 03:20.500 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
records and at least two deaths
in Arizona
are blamed on the heat.
Conditions are also

03:20.534 --> 03:24.638 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
making it even tougher to
control wildfires
across the region.

03:24.671 --> 03:29.509 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: There will be no
federal criminal
charges in the case of a Georgia
teenager

03:29.543 --> 03:35.315 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
who suffocated inside a
rolled-up gym mat.
Kendrick Johnson died at his
Valdosta high

03:35.348 --> 03:42.522 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
school in January 2013. Local
officials ruled
he got stuck trying to reach a
gym shoe. That

03:42.556 --> 03:46.993 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
prompted rallies and marches,
but, today,
the Justice Department said
there's not enough

03:47.027 --> 03:49.029 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
evidence to prove a crime.

03:49.062 --> 03:53.667 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The British
Parliament convened
in special session today to pay
tribute one

03:53.700 --> 03:59.106 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of its own, Jo Cox. The Labor
Party member
was shot and stabbed to death
last week in

03:59.139 --> 04:05.979 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
her home district. Lawmakers
recalled Cox's
life and work, and placed two
roses, one white

04:06.012 --> 04:11.618 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
for her home county of Yorkshire
and one red
for the Labor Party, at her
now-vacant seat.

04:11.651 --> 04:16.790 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RACHEL REEVES, Labor Party M.P.:
Jo was struck
down much too soon, so it now
falls on all

04:16.823 --> 04:22.229 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of our shoulders, the woman I
met in the coffee
shop in Batley, Jo's friends,
M.P.s, all of

04:22.262 --> 04:28.969 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
us, to carry on Jo's work, to
combat and guard
against hatred, intolerance, and
injustice,

04:29.002 --> 04:33.306 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to serve others with dignity and
with love.
And that is the best way that we
can remember

04:33.340 --> 04:35.775 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Jo and all that she stood for.

04:35.809 --> 04:41.281 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: After a three-day
halt, campaigning
resumed today on whether Britain
should stay

04:41.314 --> 04:44.784 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the European Union. The
referendum will
be held Thursday.

04:44.818 --> 04:50.557 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Wall Street surged
today, on optimism
that Britain will vote to stay
in the E.U.

04:50.590 --> 04:58.365 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Dow Jones industrial average
gained 129
points to close near 17805. The
Nasdaq rose

04:58.398 --> 05:02.202 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
almost 37 points, and the S&amp;P
500 added 12.

05:02.235 --> 05:07.841 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: A record 65
million people
were forced from their homes
worldwide last

05:07.874 --> 05:13.547 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
year, largely by war. That's
roughly equal
to the entire population of
Great Britain.

05:13.580 --> 05:19.653 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The U.N.'s refugee agency
reports more than
half were fleeing conflicts in
Syria, Afghanistan

05:19.686 --> 05:25.792 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and Somalia. And while millions
escaped to
other nations, many more are on
the run within

05:25.825 --> 05:27.594 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
their own countries.

05:27.627 --> 05:32.399 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Iran says it has
broken up one
of the largest terror plots ever
on its soil.

05:32.432 --> 05:38.405 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
State TV today reported police
arrested several
suspects and seized bombs and
ammunition.

05:38.438 --> 05:44.144 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It suggested the Islamic State
or other Sunni
militants may be to blame. Iran
is supporting

05:44.177 --> 05:46.913 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the fight against ISIS in Iraq
and Syria.

05:46.947 --> 05:52.619 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And China leads
the world in
supercomputers for the seventh
year in a row.

05:52.652 --> 05:58.358 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
An annual ranking out today also
finds that,
for the first time, China has
more machines

05:58.391 --> 06:05.765 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
than the U.S. on the list. One
is five times
faster than the fastest U.S.
supercomputer.

06:05.799 --> 06:12.005 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Still to come on the "NewsHour":
the gun debate
continues in Congress and in
court; a humanitarian

06:12.038 --> 06:20.213 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
crisis unveiled as Iraqi forces
retake Fallujah;
a major shakeup in the Donald
Trump campaign;

06:20.247 --> 06:27.120 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and much more.

06:27.153 --> 06:36.162 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: In the wake of the
deadly Orlando
nightclub shooting, the debate
over gun violence

06:36.196 --> 06:39.299 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
faced a series of votes on
Capitol Hill.

06:39.332 --> 06:41.201 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Lisa Desjardins reports.

06:41.234 --> 06:47.507 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: From
courtrooms, to Congress,
the often theoretical debate
over guns touched

06:47.540 --> 06:52.178 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ground today, eight days after
the massacre
in Orlando.

06:52.212 --> 06:57.317 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Washington, a showdown on the
Senate floor
over four different gun control
measures,

06:57.350 --> 07:02.555 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
from background checks to
banning sales to
those on the no-fly list. It was
a classic

07:02.589 --> 07:04.457 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
partisan duel.

07:04.491 --> 07:09.429 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SEN. HARRY REID (D-NV), MINORITY
LEADER: Republicans
say hey, look, we tried. And all
the time,

07:09.462 --> 07:12.832 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
they're cheerleaders for bosses
at the NRA.

07:12.866 --> 07:19.272 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SEN. JOHN CORNYN (R), Texas: Our
colleagues
want to make this about gun
control. My colleagues

07:19.306 --> 07:22.475 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
many ways want to fight the
symptoms without
fighting the disease.

07:22.509 --> 07:27.247 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Lots of debate,
but no expected
changes, when all was said and
done.

07:27.280 --> 07:32.085 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Across the street, Supreme Court
justices
decided not to hear an appeal of
semiautomatic

07:32.118 --> 07:37.357 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
weapons bans in Connecticut and
New York.
That means the bans stay in
place. They were

07:37.390 --> 07:42.295 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
enacted after the school
shooting in 2012,
at Newtown, Connecticut.

07:42.329 --> 07:47.000 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Families of the Newtown victims
were also
watching this courtroom in
Bridgeport, where

07:47.033 --> 07:51.871 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a state judge heard arguments
about whether
they can sue a gun manufacturer.
James Vogts

07:51.905 --> 07:56.743 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
represents Remington Arms, which
made the
semiautomatic rifle used in the
Newtown shooting.

07:56.776 --> 07:58.545 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES VOGTS, Remington Arms:
It's really not
the role of this court, or
perhaps a jury,

07:58.578 --> 08:07.187 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to decide whether civilians, as
a class, broad
class of people, are not
appropriate to own

08:07.220 --> 08:09.055 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
these class of firearms.

08:09.089 --> 08:12.559 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Joshua Koskoff
represents
the families who are suing.

08:12.592 --> 08:16.830 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOSHUA KOSKOFF, Attorney For
Plaintiffs: It
was an AR-15 rifle, a weapon,
Judge, that

08:16.863 --> 08:24.771 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
was designed to be used in
combat by our military
to assault and kill enemies of
war. It was

08:24.804 --> 08:30.610 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Remington's choice to entrust
the most notorious
American military killing
machine to the public.

08:30.643 --> 08:35.548 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Recent polls
show Americans
generally support gun
restrictions. In a Reuters/Ipsos

08:35.582 --> 08:41.821 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
survey last week, about 71
percent approved
of strong or moderate gun
restrictions, while

08:41.855 --> 08:47.427 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
about 16 percent want basic
limits and just
6 percent said firearms should
have no or

08:47.460 --> 08:49.362 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
few restrictions.

08:49.396 --> 08:54.401 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, as debate continues, so
does the violence.
In Chicago yesterday, police
reported something

08:54.434 --> 09:00.306 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
rare, an apparent gang-related
shooting using
not a handgun, but a
semiautomatic assault

09:00.340 --> 09:01.975 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
rifle.

09:02.008 --> 09:06.479 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN: When does it stop? What's
going to
-- how do we get help with this?
What do we

09:06.513 --> 09:07.680 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
do?

09:07.714 --> 09:10.417 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: The Chicago
victim was 17
years old.

09:10.450 --> 09:15.221 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: For more on the
recurring debate
over gun laws and gun ownership,
we turn now

09:15.255 --> 09:19.859 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to Marcia Coyle, "NewsHour"
regular and chief
Washington correspondent for
"The National

09:19.893 --> 09:24.531 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Law Journal," Evan Osnos, whose
extensive
report on concealed-carry laws
appears in

09:24.564 --> 09:28.968 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
this week's "New Yorker"
magazine, and, as
you just heard, "NewsHour"
correspondent Lisa

09:29.002 --> 09:32.572 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Desjardins, who's been following
the action
on Capitol Hill.

09:32.605 --> 09:37.510 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As of now, this time 6:00 p.m.
Eastern time
tonight, do we have any -- is
there any possibility

09:37.544 --> 09:40.914 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that any of the four gun bills
that were up
for a vote today might pass?

09:40.947 --> 09:43.850 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Realistically,
no. And we
already know that one has
failed, something

09:43.883 --> 09:48.354 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that seems innocuous, increasing
funding for
background checks on the federal
level. That

09:48.388 --> 09:50.123 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
has not received 60 votes.

09:50.156 --> 09:54.694 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It was Republican amendment.
That didn't clear.
We do not expect the other three
to clear

09:54.727 --> 09:56.095 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
there that 60-vote bar either.

09:56.129 --> 09:58.798 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: In spite of what we
just saw in
terms of public opinion?

09:58.832 --> 10:00.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: That's right.

10:00.767 --> 10:04.771 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And when you look at public
opinion here,
there's a real disconnect. You
see overwhelmingly,

10:04.804 --> 10:09.509 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
not just Americans as a whole,
Gwen, supporting
things like background checks,
some moderate

10:09.542 --> 10:12.846 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
restrictions, you could say, but
Republicans
as a group.

10:12.879 --> 10:17.617 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Recently, Pew and many other
groups have polled
Republicans and they find
80-some percent

10:17.650 --> 10:22.055 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
sometimes support background
checks, but yet
Republicans on Capitol Hill are
going the

10:22.088 --> 10:23.890 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
exact opposite directions.

10:23.923 --> 10:28.461 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Today at the Supreme
Court, Marcia,
we saw that the court decided
not to take

10:28.495 --> 10:32.799 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
up a challenge to two assault
weapons bans
in New York and Connecticut.

10:32.832 --> 10:36.903 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now, we know that when the court
doesn't do
something, that doesn't
necessarily mean a

10:36.936 --> 10:39.239 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
lot. But there's a record here.
There's a
pattern.

10:39.272 --> 10:43.142 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARCIA COYLE, "The National Law
Journal":
Well there is, the court not
wanting to get

10:43.176 --> 10:46.145 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
back into this Second Amendment
arena.

10:46.179 --> 10:52.519 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The court's had a number of
petitions come
before them in recent years.
Even this year,

10:52.552 --> 10:59.759 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
